Architecture:

- Architecture define the structure of the system
- The main type of architecture are monolithic and microservices

MONOLITHIC ARCHITECTURE:

- It is a legacy architecture
- Here all the services are defined under only 1 application
- Example : Single application hold product service,order servce, payment service and more.

Advantages:
1.Transaction management is easy since all the data is in 1 DB

Disadvantage:
1.Difficult to scale(If payment service need to modify then entire code gets modified which leads to TIGHT COUPLING)
2.IDE OVERLOAD - ide becomes slow when more files loaded

MICROSERVICE ARCHITECTURE:

- Here the application is decomposed into multiple micro(size vary based on use cases/services) services
- Example: Product,payment,order have seperate service applications

Advantages:
1.All the disadvantages of monolithic are advantages of microservices

Disadvantages:
1.Application should be properly decomposed othervise it results in TIGHTLY COUPLED
2.Difficult to manage the errors
-There are 3 services s3,s2,s1
-s2 depends on s2
-s1 depends on s1
-If s3 modified the logic
-s1,s2 doesn't know where the error occurs(Actually occurs due to the change in s3)
-tester found the error is from s2 then s2 found the error is because of s3 then everything is rectified->It make a longer process
3.Trasaction Management becomes difficult because each service has its own db

